title: LA rockers heading to Wolverhampton
text:
Tweet 
The band, who formed in California some 17 years ago, are performing at the Slade Rooms in the city on Thursday, November 26. 
Known for their hit albums Thrown to the Wolves, Welcome Home and Hello It’s Me, the band reached TV fame when they starred as the fictional band Dingoes Ate My Baby on the hit fantasy show Buffy the Vampire Slayer. Are you a fan of the band? Let us know below... 
They have also had tracks featured on American television shows such as, Party of Five, Road Rules, The Real World and Charmed. 
Tickets are priced at £13.20.
